<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About - Furry Tails Photography</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="logo">
        <a href="/">
          <img src="/gallery/logo.jpeg" alt="Logo" width="40" height="40">
          Pet Photography
        </a>
      </div>
      <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger">
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </button>
      <ul class="nav-links" id="nav-links">
        <li><a href="/gallery">GALLERY</a></li>
        <li><a href="/how-it-works">SESSIONS</a></li>
        <li><a href="/prices">PRICES</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">ABOUT</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact">CONTACT</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <!-- About Hero Section -->
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="about-hero-box">
          <div class="about-hero-text">
            <h2>About</h2>
            <p>Your pet's biggest fan with a camera</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About Content Section -->
    <section class="about-content-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="about-content-wrapper">
          <div class="about-text-and-image">
            <div class="about-content">
              <h3>Hi, I’m Anna, and I’m a pet photographer based in Berlin</h3>
              <p> with a big heart for animals.
My journey into pet photography began with a very personal loss. When my own beloved dog passed away, I spent hours searching through my computer for beautiful photos of her — only to realize I didn’t have nearly enough images I truly loved. I desperately wanted to hang a few meaningful portraits on my wall, but most of the photos just didn’t feel right. The only ones that brought me real joy were a few playful shots from her birthday party against a bright pink background.
I created my in-home pet photography studio because I believe every pet deserves to be remembered with images that capture their true personality — full of life, movement, and joy.
</p>
            </div>
            <div class="about-image">
              <img src="/gallery/me.jpg" alt="Anna, pet photographer">
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-style-box">
            <h4>My style</h4>
            <p>In my cozy living-room studio in Berlin, I work with professional lighting and a variety of colourful, cheerful backgrounds. While I do take classic portraits of pets sitting, lying, or standing beautifully, my favourite moments are the ones filled with action — the zoomies, the mid-air jumps, the silly playful expressions, and all the little quirks that make your pet uniquely lovable. These energetic, fun shots are what I love capturing the most, because they show your pet's real spirit.
I photograph every session with care and patience, and I edit every single photo by hand — no filters, just thoughtful, natural editing so the final images feel warm, vibrant, and true to your pet's character.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="about-cta">
            <div class="about-cta-content">
              <div class="about-cta-text">
                <p>Ready to capture memories with your furry friend?</p>
                <a href="/contact" class="cta-button">Get in Touch</a>
              </div>
              <div class="about-cta-image">
                <img src="/gallery/Gorgo.jpg" alt="Pet">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-grid">
        <div class="footer-col">
          <div class="footer-logo">
            <img src="/gallery/logo.jpeg" alt="Logo" width="30" height="30">
            <span>Pet Photography</span>
          </div>
          <p>Capturing the joy and personality of your beloved pets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <h4>QUICK LINKS</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/gallery">Gallery</a></li>
            <li><a href="/how-it-works">Sessions</a></li>
            <li><a href="/prices">Prices</a></li>
            <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <h4>LET'S CONNECT</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://instagram.com">Instagram</a></li>
            <li><a href="tel:+1234567890">(123) 456-7890</a></li>
            <li><a href="mailto:hello@furrytails.com">Email</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <a href="/contact" class="footer-cta">BOOK A SESSION</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-bottom">
        <p>&copy; 2026 Furry Tails Pet Photography. All rights reserved.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const hamburger = document.getElementById('hamburger');
    const navLinks = document.getElementById('nav-links');

    hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => {
      hamburger.classList.toggle('active');
      navLinks.style.display = navLinks.style.display === 'flex' ? 'none' : 'flex';
    });

    navLinks.querySelectorAll('a').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        hamburger.classList.remove('active');
        navLinks.style.display = 'none';
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
